---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Denmark Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/denmark/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Sweden for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/sweden' },
  { title: 'Norway for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/norway' },
  { title: 'Germany for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/germany' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'denmarkFit', header: 'Denmark Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'DKK 3,200-4,500/mo', denmarkFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'DKK 3,800-5,200/mo', denmarkFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'DKK 2,900-4,100/mo', denmarkFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'DKK 2,700-3,900/mo', denmarkFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Danish Public', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: 'Tax-funded', denmarkFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'DKK 2,900-4,500', annual: 'DKK 34,800-54,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'DKK 4,000-5,800', annual: 'DKK 48,000-69,600' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'DKK 5,400-7,800', annual: 'DKK 64,800-93,600' },
  { category: 'Danish Public Healthcare', monthly: 'Tax-funded', annual: 'Free for residents' },
  { category: 'Danish Private Supplement', monthly: 'DKK 400-1,200', annual: 'DKK 4,800-14,400' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Denmark 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Denmark. Public healthcare, Copenhagen hospitals, hygge lifestyle, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Denmark"
  subheadline="Denmark offers excellent tax-funded healthcare, high happiness rankings, and Scandinavian quality of life—though immigration requires meeting specific criteria."
  heroImage="/images/countries/denmark-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Denmark</h2>
  <p>
    Denmark consistently ranks among the world's happiest countries, offering excellent public services, safety, and quality of life. The healthcare system is comprehensive and free for residents. The concept of "hygge" (cozy contentment) reflects Danish culture's focus on well-being.
  </p>

  <p>
    Copenhagen combines urban sophistication with bike-friendly streets and waterfront living. Aarhus offers culture and university life. Odense has Hans Christian Andersen heritage. Smaller towns provide peaceful retirement with good healthcare access throughout the country.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Excellent; tax-funded universal system</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Danish; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> DKK 18,000-30,000/month (~€2,400-4,000); high by EU standards</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Maritime; mild but dark winters</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> EU member (not Eurozone; uses DKK)</li>
      <li><strong>Cycling:</strong> Excellent bike infrastructure; flat terrain</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Denmark's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Denmark's healthcare is tax-funded and free at point of use for residents. The system is organized into five regions, each managing hospitals and healthcare services. Quality is excellent with modern facilities and well-trained staff.
  </p>

  <p>
    GPs act as gatekeepers to specialist care. Wait times for some specialists can be weeks to months. Emergency care is immediate and excellent. Dental care for adults is not covered; many add private dental insurance.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">GP Assignment</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Once registered, you're assigned to a GP practice near your home. You can request to change, but choice is limited in some areas. Private insurance allows direct specialist access without GP referral, which some seniors prefer.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Denmark's immigration for non-EU retirees is restrictive:
  </p>

  <h3>Family Reunification</h3>
  <p>
    If you have a Danish citizen or resident spouse/partner, family reunification is possible. Age requirements and attachment conditions apply. Your Danish family member must meet income requirements.
  </p>

  <h3>Self-Employment</h3>
  <p>
    Starting a business in Denmark can provide residence. Must demonstrate viable business and economic benefit to Denmark. Not strictly retirement but possible for active retirees.
  </p>

  <h3>EU/EEA Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement applies. Register with Danish authorities after 3 months. Must demonstrate sufficient resources and health coverage. After registration, access Danish healthcare with yellow health card.
  </p>

  <h3>No Retirement Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Denmark doesn't offer a retirement visa for non-EU nationals. You need qualifying circumstances like family, work, or business.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Denmark:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence application:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC initially; register for yellow health card</li>
    <li><strong>After registration:</strong> Full access to Danish public healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Private option:</strong> For faster specialist access and dental coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Denmark</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for residence applications. Once you have your yellow health card (sundhedskort), Danish healthcare is free. Many residents add private insurance (sundhedsforsikring) for faster specialist access and dental. Keep international coverage for travel.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Denmark, these providers offer appropriate coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Denmark</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Scandinavian network, good for initial period</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive European pricing</li>
    <li><strong>Danish Private:</strong> Dansk Sundhedssikring, Tryg offer local supplements</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Denmark.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Denmark reflect high local prices:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Get registered:</strong> Danish public healthcare is free once you have yellow card</li>
    <li><strong>Private Danish:</strong> Cheaper than international once resident (~DKK 500-1,000/month)</li>
    <li><strong>Denmark exclusion:</strong> Once in public system, exclude Denmark from international</li>
    <li><strong>Dental separate:</strong> Danish dental insurance is affordable (~DKK 200-400/month)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American with Danish Spouse, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Married to Danish citizen. Moving to Copenhagen via family reunification.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for application. After yellow card, Danish system covers care. Keep Cigna for US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially ~DKK 4,000/month. After: public free + Cigna ~DKK 2,500/month (Denmark excluded).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: German EU Citizen, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Retiring from Hamburg to Aarhus. German pension €2,200/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EHIC initially. Register for yellow card. Add Danish private for faster specialist access.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Public free + Danish private ~DKK 800/month + Allianz for Germany ~DKK 2,000/month.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Swedish Retiree, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Nordic citizen moving from Malmö to Copenhagen. Swedish pension.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Nordic agreement allows easy transfer. Register, get yellow card, access Danish healthcare.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Danish public free. Optional private supplement ~DKK 600/month for faster care.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can non-EU retirees move to Denmark?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very difficult without Danish family connection. Denmark doesn't have a retirement visa. You typically need: Danish spouse/partner (family reunification), work permit, or business. Pure financial independence isn't a pathway like in some countries.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Danish healthcare really free?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        For residents with a yellow health card, yes. GP visits, hospital care, specialists (via referral), and most prescriptions have no direct charge. Dental care for adults, some physiotherapy, and psychologist services are not covered. Many add private insurance for these.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the "attachment requirement"?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        For family reunification, Denmark assesses whether the couple's combined ties to Denmark exceed ties to other countries. If your Danish spouse lived abroad for many years, this can be problematic. It's designed to ensure genuine connection to Denmark.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How expensive is Denmark really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very expensive. Copenhagen is one of Europe's priciest cities. However, once you have healthcare access (free) and if housing is sorted, daily costs are manageable. Restaurant meals are expensive; cooking at home is reasonable. Public transport is excellent but not cheap.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Denmark.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Danish immigration and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
